cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE

The paper deals with the verification of distributed protocols, which involves reasoning about an unbounded number of nodes and messages. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Logic (cs.LO), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), or Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The use of effectively propositional logic (EPR) and first-order logic also supports the possibility of the paper belonging to the Logic sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO, followed by cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.DS, and cs.SE.
